The paper discusses the use of photonic delay systems for machine learning, specifically using gradient descent with backpropagation through time to optimize input encoding. This falls under the category of neural networks and their applications (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves the use of electronic and photonic devices for computation, which could fall under the categories of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET), information theory (cs.IT), and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the optimized system, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
